---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Top 20 Geography Quiz Questions | QuizZone Blog"
  description="Test your geography knowledge with these top 20 questions covering capitals, landmarks, oceans, mountains, and more from around the world."
  canonical="/blog/top-geography-quiz-questions"
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 flex items-center gap-2">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-blue-600">Home</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-600">Blog</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <span class="text-gray-600">Geography Questions</span>
    </nav>
    <article>
      <header class="mb-10">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Geography</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">May 20, 2024 · 4 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
          Top 20 Geography Quiz Questions You Must Try
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          How well do you know planet Earth? These geography questions range from easy capitals to tricky physical geography that'll stump even seasoned travellers.
        </p>
      </header>
      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-6">
        <p class="text-gray-600">Geography is one of the most popular trivia categories. Here are 20 of the best questions to challenge your geographical knowledge:</p>
        {[
          { q: 'What is the longest river in the world?', a: 'The Nile (approximately 6,650 km)' },
          { q: 'Which country has the most natural lakes?', a: 'Canada' },
          { q: 'What is the capital of Japan?', a: 'Tokyo' },
          { q: 'On which continent is the Sahara Desert?', a: 'Africa' },
          { q: 'What is the tallest mountain in the world?', a: 'Mount Everest (8,848.86 m)' },
          { q: 'Which country contains most of the Amazon Rainforest?', a: 'Brazil (about 60%)' },
          { q: 'What is the smallest country in the world?', a: 'Vatican City' },
          { q: 'Which ocean is the largest?', a: 'The Pacific Ocean' },
          { q: 'What is the capital of Canada?', a: 'Ottawa' },
          { q: 'Which country is home to the Great Barrier Reef?', a: 'Australia' },
        ].map((item, i) => (
          <div class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-100 rounded-xl p-5">
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2"><span class="text-green-600">Q{i + 1}.</span> {item.q}</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-green-700 font-medium">✅ {item.a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-100 rounded-2xl p-6 text-center">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Test Your Geography Skills!</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-500 mb-4">Play the full Geography quiz on QuizZone with timer and scoring.</p>
          <a href="/quiz/geography" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-bold rounded-xl transition-colors shadow-md">Play Geography Quiz →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
